step.tex:
\text{Using step 1}\\
\int \dfrac{x^3 + 3x + 4 }{\sqrt{x}}\,dx = \int\left( x^{\dfrac{5}{2}} +3x^{\dfrac{1}{2}} +4 x^{-\dfrac{1}{2}}\right)dx\\ \qquad\qquad= \dfrac{x^{\dfrac{5}{2}+1}}{\left(\dfrac{5}{2}+1\right)}+\dfrac{3x^{\dfrac{1}{2} + 1}}{\left(\dfrac{1}{2}+1\right)} +\dfrac{4 x^{-\dfrac{1}{2}+1}}{\left(-\dfrac{1}{2}+1\right)} \\ \qquad\qquad=\dfrac{2}{7}x^{\dfrac{7}{2}}+ 2 x^{\dfrac{3}{2}} + 8x^{\dfrac{1}{2}} + C\\ \qquad\qquad=\dfrac{2}{7}x^{\dfrac{7}{2}}+ 2 x^{\dfrac{3}{2}} + 8\sqrt{x} + C\\
\text{Here, C is the constant of integration.}

